**Distance & Time:**
- The Lincoln Memorial is approximately **0.8 miles (1.3 km)** west-northwest of the White House
- **Walking time:** About 15-20 minutes
- **Driving time:** About 5-10 minutes (though parking can be challenging)

**Walking Route (Most Popular):**
The best way to experience the journey is to walk:
1. Exit the White House and head west toward the Ellipse (the large oval park south of the White House)
2. Continue west past the Ellipse
3. Head toward the National Mall area
4. Follow the paths through the National Mall westward
5. You'll reach the Lincoln Memorial at the western end of the Mall

This walking route takes you through some of Washington DC's most iconic areas and is very scenic, especially if you explore the National Mall along the way.

**Alternative Options:**
- **Metro:** You could take the Metro to the Foggy Bottom-GWU station or L'Enfant Plaza, though walking from the White House is often more direct
- **Taxi/Uber:** Quick option if you prefer not to walk, though traffic in downtown DC can be slow

The walk is very pleasant and recommended if weather permits!
